==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foolscap
<hw>Fools"cap`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So called from the
watermark of a <ets>fool's cap and bells</ets> used by old paper makers.
See <ets>Fool's cap</ets>, under <er>Fool</er>.]</ety> <def>A writing
paper made in sheets, ordinarily 16 x 13 inches, and folded so as to
make a page 13 x 8 inches. See <er>Paper</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

